CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 10, 1946, pg. 8 reads: "Frog Week Visitors - Taking a gay part in most glamorous Frog Week since its inception were the quintet shown above. Front, pretty Mrs. Conklin Collum of Cleveland, Mrs. Epsie Morgan of Philly and Mrs. J.J. Thompson of Detroit.  Standing are W. Rollo Wilson, famous sportswriter of Philly, guest of the Richard Joneses, and Mr. Thompson of Detroit, who, with his wife, were guests of the Sauel Wynns. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait, seated from left: Mrs. Conklin Collum, Epsie Morgan, and Mrs. J. J.Thompson; standing: W. Rollo Wilson and J.J. Thompson, gathered in Loendi Club for FROGS week event
